{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1784A","heading":"Examination and treatment for emergency medical conditions and women in labor","label":"1784A Examination and treatment for emergency medical conditions and women in labor","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptII/ch17/schVIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In the case of a hospital of the Department that has an emergency department, if any individual comes to the hospital or the campus of the hospital and a request is made on behalf of the individual for examination or treatment for a medical condition, the hospital must provide for an appropriate medical screening examination within the capability of the emergency department, including ancillary services routinely available to the emergency department, to determine whether or not an emergency medical condition exists.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Necessary Stabilizing Treatment for Emergency Medical Conditions and Labor","label":"b .—Necessary Stabilizing Treatment for Emergency Medical Conditions and Labor","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"within the staff and facilities available at the hospital, for such further medical examination and such treatment as may be required to stabilize the medical condition; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for transfer of the individual to another medical facility in accordance with subsection (c).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A hospital is deemed to meet the requirement of paragraph (1)(A) with respect to an individual if the hospital offers the individual the further medical examination and treatment described in that paragraph and informs the individual (or a person acting on behalf of the individual) of the risks and benefits to the individual of such examination and treatment, but the individual (or a person acting on behalf of the individual) refuses to consent to the examination and treatment. The hospital shall take all reasonable steps to secure the written informed consent of the individual (or person) to refuse such examination and treatment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A hospital is deemed to meet the requirement of paragraph (1)(B) with respect to an individual if the hospital offers to transfer the individual to another medical facility in accordance with subsection (c) and informs the individual (or a person acting on behalf of the individual) of the risks and benefits to the individual of such transfer, but the individual (or a person acting on behalf of the individual) refuses to consent to the transfer. The hospital shall take all reasonable steps to secure the written informed consent of the individual (or person) to refuse such transfer.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Restricting Transfers Until Individual Stabilized","label":"c .—Restricting Transfers Until Individual Stabilized","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the individual (or a legally responsible person acting on behalf of the individual), after being informed of the obligations of the hospital under this section and of the risk of transfer, requests, in writing, transfer to another medical facility;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a physician of the Department has signed a certification that, based upon the information available at the time of transfer, the medical benefits reasonably expected from the provision of appropriate medical treatment at another medical facility outweigh the increased risks to the individual and, in the case of labor, to the unborn child from effecting the transfer; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F1%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if a physician of the Department is not physically present in the emergency department at the time an individual is transferred, a qualified medical person (as defined by the Secretary for purposes of this section) has signed a certification described in clause (ii) after a physician of the Department, in consultation with the person, has made the determination described in such clause, and subsequently countersigns the certification; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the transfer is an appropriate transfer to that facility.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A certification described in clause (ii) or (iii) of paragraph (1)(A) shall include a summary of the risks and benefits upon which the certification is based.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in which the transferring hospital provides the medical treatment within its capacity that minimizes the risks to the health of the individual and, in the case of a woman in labor, the health of the unborn child;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has available space and qualified personnel for the treatment of the individual; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has agreed to accept transfer of the individual and to provide appropriate medical treatment;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"observations of signs or symptoms;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"preliminary diagnosis;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FC%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"treatment provided;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FC%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the results of any tests; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FC%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the informed written request or certification (or copy thereof) provided under paragraph (1)(A);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in which the transfer is effected through qualified personnel and transportation equipment, including the use of necessary and medically appropriate life support measures during the transfer; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fc%2F3%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that meets such other requirements as the Secretary considers necessary in the interest of the health and safety of the individual or individuals transferred.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Payment to the Department","label":"d .—Payment to the Department","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall charge for any care or services provided under this section in accordance with billing and reimbursement authorities available to the Secretary under other provisions of law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Definitions","label":"e .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the physical area immediately adjacent to the main buildings of the hospital;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other areas and structures that are not strictly contiguous to the main buildings but are located not more than 250 yards from the main buildings; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other areas determined by the Secretary to be part of the campus of the hospital.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"placing the health of the individual (or, with respect to a pregnant woman, the health of the woman or her unborn child) in serious jeopardy;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"serious impairment to bodily functions; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"serious dysfunction of any bodily organ or part; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that there is inadequate time to effect a safe transfer to another hospital before delivery; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that transfer may pose a threat to the health or safety of the woman or the unborn child.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"with respect to an emergency medical condition described in paragraph (2)(A), to provide such medical treatment of the condition as may be necessary to assure, within reasonable medical probability, that no material deterioration of the condition is likely to result from or occur during the transfer of the individual from a facility; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"with respect to an emergency medical condition described in paragraph (2)(B), to deliver (including the placenta).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"with respect to an emergency medical condition described in paragraph (2)(A), that no material deterioration of the condition is likely, within reasonable medical probability, to result from or occur during the transfer of the individual from a facility; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"with respect to an emergency medical condition described in paragraph (2)(B), that the woman has delivered (including the placenta).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has been declared dead; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1784A/e/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs1784A%2Fe%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"leaves the facility without the permission of any such person.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
